1. User (Abstract Class)
The User class is an abstract class that represents a general user in the system, and it inherited by Student and Lecturer Class.

Attributes:
•	userID – Unique identifier for each user
•	password – User account password
•	email – User email address
•	username – User’s name in the system
Methods:
•	login() – Allows users to log into system
•	logout() – Allows users to log out of the system
•	updateProfile() – Allows users to update their personal information


2. Student Class
The Student class inherits from the User class and it represents students who use the system.
Attributes:
•	studentID – Unique identifier for the student
•	major – The student’s field of study
•	enrolledDate – The date the student enrolled
Methods:
•	viewAssignments() – Allows students to view their assignments
•	msrkAsCompleted() – Allows students to mark assignments as completed
•	viewDashboard() – Display an overview of assignments and submission



3. Lecturer Class
The Lecturer class also inherits from the User class and represents lecturers who manage assignments in the system.
Attributes:
•	staffID – Unique identifier for the lecturer
•	department – The lecturer’s department
•	officeLocation – Location of the lecturer’s office
Methods:
•	viewAssignments() – Allows students to view their assignments
•	msrkAsCompleted() – Allows students to mark assignments as completed
•	viewSubmissions() – Allows lecturers to review student submissions

4. Assignment Class
The Assignment class represents assignments created by lecturers and completed by students.
Attributes:
•	assignmentID – Unique identifier for the assignment
•	title – Assignment title
•	description – Assignment description
•	dueDate – The deadline for submission
•	status – Current status of the assignment
Methods:
•	updateStatus() – Update the assignment status
•	calculatePenalty() – Calculates late submission penalties
•	delete() – Removes the assignment from the system






5. Submission Class
The Submission class represents the assignments submitted by students.
Attributes:
•	submissionID – Unique identifier for the submission
•	fileURL – Location of the submitted file
•	submittedAt – Date and time the assignment was submitted
•	grade – Grade given by the lecturer
•	feedback – Lecturer’s comments on the submission
Methods:
•	updateFile() – Allows students to upload assignment files

6. Notification Class
The Notification class handles reminders and notifications sent to users.
Attributes:
•	notiID – Unique identifier for the notification
•	message – Notification content
•	timestamp – Time the notification was sent
Methods:
•	sendReminder() – Sends assignment reminders to users
•	markAsRead() – Marks the notification as read








Relationships Between Classes
•	User  Student / Lecturer
This is an inheritance relationship where both Student and Lecturer inherit common attributes and methods from User.
•	Lecturer  Assignment (1:N)
One lecturer can create many assignments.
•	Student  Assignment (N:N)
A student can have multiple assignments, and each assignment can be assigned to multiple students.
•	Assignment  Submission (1:N)
One assignment can have many submissions.
•	Student  Submission (1:N)
One student can submit multiple assignments.
•	User  Notification (1:N)
One user can receive multiple notification.
